---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Tobiloba Adeyemo"
  description="Privacy policy for tobilobaadeyemo.com — what information is collected, how it is used, and your rights under POPIA."
>
  <section>
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="kicker">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 12 June 2026</p>

      <h2>Who I am</h2>
      <p>
        This website, tobilobaadeyemo.com, is operated by Tobiloba Adeyemo, a cloud security
        engineer based in Gauteng, South Africa ("I", "me").
      </p>

      <h2>What information is collected</h2>
      <p>
        This site does not use accounts, tracking pixels, or advertising. Information I receive is
        limited to what you choose to send me directly — for example when you contact me via
        WhatsApp or LinkedIn: your name, contact details, and the content of your message.
      </p>
      <p>
        Standard server logs (IP address, browser type, pages requested) may be kept by the
        hosting provider for security and operational purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>How it is used</h2>
      <p>
        Only to respond to your enquiry and deliver services you request. I do not sell, rent, or
        share your personal information with third parties for marketing.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact me via WhatsApp or LinkedIn, those platforms process your data under their
        own privacy policies. Outbound links on this site (LinkedIn, GitHub, Credly) lead to
        services with their own terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights (POPIA)</h2>
      <p>
        Under South Africa's Protection of Personal Information Act, you may request access to,
        correction of, or deletion of personal information I hold about you. Contact me via the
        details on the <a href="/#contact">contact section</a> to exercise these rights.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>Updates to this policy will be posted on this page with a revised date.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
